" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 527 "a.  x-intercepts are -3 and \+
5.\nb. f10 is >0 with values of x from -infinity to -3 and from 5 to  \+
+infinity.\nc.  f10 is <0 for values of x from (-3, 5).\nd.  y-interce
pt is -15\ne.  As x approaches -infinity, f10 approaches +infinity.  A
s x approaches +infinity, f10 approaches +infinity.\nf.  Critical poin
t is at x=1.\ng.  There is no local max.\nh.  The local min is at (1,-
16).\ni.  The function values are increasing for values of x from (1, \+
+infinity).\nj.  The function values are decreasing for values of x fr
om (-infinity, 1)." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
